description:
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for passionate and committed Health Care Assistants to join our innovative community nursing team at &lt;strong&gt;Haworth Medical Practice&lt;/strong&gt;. We offer a range of career opportunities working with our diverse communities across the district.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ll support your personal and professional development, including our preceptorship programme that is tailored to meet your needs, and your continued clinical development to further develop your skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a high-performing, learning organisation, you will also benefit from our coaching and mentoring programme to support your development goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a community health care assistant, you will work within a dynamic, forward thinking district nursing service that ensures the delivery of high quality care to a practice population. You will work as part of a skill-mix team, undertaking appropriate delegated duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be working on a rota basis as part of a seven-day service, with the support of agile technology to help you deliver timely, high quality care, with support from specialists across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care experience and an NVQ level 3 or equivalent is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Extensive regular travel across the district is a requirement of the role in order to successfully undertake the range of duties specified within the job description. Therefore, it is an essential that applicants have the ability to travel regularly across the district to meet the needs and demands of the service. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We aim to shortlist on the 2nd December 2020 and interview on the 22nd &amp;/or 23rd December, however these are provisional dates and may change. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Rae, Service Manager Airedale/Wharfedale &amp; Out of Hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rebecca.rae@bdct.nhs.uk / 07701280142&lt;/p&gt;
